section.def:
API data (預報乘客資料), in
            relation to a traveller, means—(a)the following information set out in the traveller’s specified travel
                    document—(i)the traveller’s family name and given name;(ii)the traveller’s date of birth;(iii)the traveller’s gender;(iv)the traveller’s nationality;(v)the type of the specified travel document;(vi)the number of that travel document;(vii)the expiry date of that travel document; and(viii)the issuing state, place or organization of that travel document;
                        and(b)the traveller’s status (whether the traveller is a passenger or a member of
                    the crew of an aircraft and whether the traveller is in transit);

operator (經營人), in
            relation to an aircraft, means the person having the management of the aircraft for the
            time being or, in relation to a time, at that time;
